#: ../../source/locations-specific.rst:58 ../../source/locations-specific.rst:58
msgid "Data are marked ``accepted`` when all of the data can be entered in accordance with the guidance of this handbook. The ``conflict`` flag is used whenever there is a conflicts with another location and a review shows it to be the incorrect or false location. A :ref:`public_notes:meta <notes-location>` should always accompany any ``conflict`` flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/locations-specific.rst:60 ../../source/locations-specific.rst:60
msgid "If the data itself cannot be brought into the SFM standard the flag ``issue`` should be used. Finally, if it cannot be established whether a location should be flagged as ``accepted`` or ``conflict`` then the flag ``work_needed`` should be used as additional research is needed."
msgstr ""

